This paper deals with the problem of compacting orthogonal drawings, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph drawing (cs.GR). The algorithm presented in the paper involves altering the shape of edges, which could be seen as a data structure problem (cs.DS). The experimental evaluation involves measuring the total edge length and drawing area, which could be seen as a discrete mathematics problem (cs.DM). Finally, the use of additional bends in the edges could be seen as a trade-off between geometric results and complexity, which could be seen as a problem in social and information networks (cs.SI).
